  "body": "\r\n## 📝 Description\r\n\r\nThis patch introduces a custom handling for the mergeProps function in the vanilla package. It makes sure that the style prop is always a string.\r\n\r\n## ⛳️ Current behavior (updates)\r\n\r\nCurrently when using mergeProps the style prop results in `style=\"[object Object]\"` in the dom. \r\nThis can be reproduced for example when extending the the hidden select part in `examples/vanilla-ts/src/select.ts` with an additional prop.\r\n\r\n```ts\r\nconst hiddenSelect = this.rootEl.querySelector<HTMLSelectElement>(\".select-hidden-select\")\r\nif (hiddenSelect) {\r\n    const mergedProps = mergeProps(this.api.getHiddenSelectProps(), {\r\n\t    'data-something': 'some-value',\r\n    });\r\n    this.spreadProps(hiddenSelect, mergedProps)\r\n}\r\n```\r\n\r\n## 🚀 New behavior\r\n\r\nNow the mergeProps function converts the style prop to a string if needed.\r\n\r\n## 💣 Is this a breaking change (Yes/No):\r\n\r\nNo\r\n",
